Class MultimediaApplet

  • java.lang.Object

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    MultimediaRootPaneContainer, java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable, javax.accessibility.Accessible, javax.swing.RootPaneContainer

    public abstract class MultimediaApplet
extends javax.swing.JApplet
implements MultimediaRootPaneContainer
    A MultimediaApplet is a JApplet that delegates all calls to "transition" methods to a MultimediaApp. The calls to the MultimediaApp object's "transition" methods will be made in the event dispatch thread. Note: The browser/appletviewer is not supposed to call the "transition" methods in the event dispatch thread. This class checks to make sure [since SwingUtilities.invokeAndWait() must not be called in the event dispatch thread]. While there is a small performance penalty incurred as a result, the "transition" methods are not called frequently enough for this to matter.
    See Also:
    "The Design and Implementation of Multimedia Software (c) 2011", Serialized Form
